topic.title: Non-Buck Mode Current Consumption (HB_WS)

body.p: Non-buck mode may be used when VBATT is less than 2.5 V. In non-buck mode, the battery supply is connected directly to VBATT and VSUP, and a supply greater than 1.62 V is connected to VDDIO.
Current consumption is with VBATT equal to 1.20 V, VDDIO equal to 1.8 V, 25 Â°C and non-buck mode.

Flash page erase or write operation
VDDIO supply current with IO static and flash idle

li.p: Measured in continuous TX or RX mode with core 0 idle at 4 MHz and peripherals disabled.
Advertising in three channels using the Low-Power Advertising (LOWPAD) application and TX packet length of 27 bytes.
The flash is supplied by VDDIO and when idle consumes a small amount of DC current.
Programming is inhibited if the VBATT voltage drops below 1 V.
